DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$x1=random(1,6,1);
$x2= $x1 + random(1,6,1);
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The value of \( \displaystyle \int_{$x1}^{$x2} \frac{1}{ x^2 } dx\) is
$PAR
\{ans_rule(20)\}

EOT
$ans1= -1/($x2) +1/$x1;

ANS(num_cmp($ans1));

&SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT'));

$SOL $BR $BR

Here we use the integration rule \( \displaystyle \int u^n du = \frac{u^{n+1}}{n+1}\):
\[
\begin{align*}
\int_{$x1}^{$x2} \frac 1 {x^2} dx
&=	\int_{$x1}^{$x2} x^{-2} dx	\\\\
&=	\left (-1)x^{-1} \right|_{$x1}^{$x2} =
		\left \frac{-1}{x} \right|_{$x1}^{$x2}	\\\\
&=	\frac{-1}{$x2} - \frac{-1}{$x1}	= \frac 1 {$x1} - \frac 1 {$x2} = $ans1
\end{align*}
\]

EOT

